          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>I am a <html:em>Quantitative Researcher</html:em> in <fr:link href="https://www.mediobanca.com/en/index.html" type="external">Mediobanca</fr:link> in London. I am also a <html:em>Research Assistant</html:em> in <fr:link href="https://thalesians.com/" type="external">Thalesians</fr:link>, supervised under <fr:link href="https://profiles.imperial.ac.uk/paul.bilokon01" type="external">Dr. Paul Bilokon</fr:link>.</html:p>
            <html:p>I am an alumni of <html:em>MSc Mathematics and Finance</html:em> in Imperial College. I am also an alumni of <fr:link href="/thoughts-emo-0001/" title="What Cambridge gave me..." uri="https://sez.moe/thoughts-emo-0001/" display-uri="thoughts-emo-0001" type="local">University of Cambridge</fr:link> as a <html:em><fr:link href="https://archive.thetab.com/uk/cambridge/2017/02/16/what-actually-date-mathmo-89152" type="external">Mathmo</fr:link></html:em> <html:em>(BA Mathematics Tripos)</html:em>.</html:p>
            <html:p>My primary research interest focuses on algebraic aspects in stochastic analysis. You may find more information on the <fr:link href="/0008/" title="Research" uri="https://sez.moe/0008/" display-uri="0008" type="local">research</fr:link> page. Currently, I am working on a paper formalising market dynamics using a game-theoretical framework, and furthermore, under a game semantical interpretation.</html:p>
            <html:p>Previously in Imperial, I was supervised by <fr:link href="https://profiles.imperial.ac.uk/thomas.cass" type="external">Prof. Thomas Cass</fr:link>, who had provided me with insights in Rough Path Theory. When I was In Cambridge, I was supervised by <fr:link href="https://www.dpmms.cam.ac.uk/~sjw47/" type="external">Prof. Simon Wadsley</fr:link>, <fr:link href="https://www.homerton.cam.ac.uk/people/anthony-ashton" type="external">Prof. Anthony Ashton</fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.dpmms.cam.ac.uk/person/jmeh1" type="external">Prof. Martin Hyland</fr:link>, and worked on researches generalising semantical correspondences of commutative submonads in ambient categories.</html:p>
            <html:p>I use NixOS on my personal devices. I also maintain an Emacs configuration file.</html:p>
            <html:p>I am a member of <fr:link href="https://www.libdems.org.uk/" type="external">UK Liberal Democrats</fr:link></html:p>
            <html:p>I currently live in Shoreditch, London. I'll be more than happy if you would like to have a coffee chat with me.</html:p>
